# The container image only needs the task code (src/) and its runtime
# dependency list (requirements.txt). Everything else — docs, tests, build
# tooling, the dev-environment stack, IDE/VCS files — is excluded so the
# image stays small and never ships anything it doesn't execute.
#
# This is an allowlist: ignore everything, then re-include only what the
# image needs, so docs/config added later can't silently bloat the image.

# Ignore everything by default...
*

# ...then re-include only what the container needs at build/run time.
!src/
!requirements.txt

# ...but never ship Python bytecode or caches, even from under src/.
**/__pycache__/
**/*.py[cod]
